definitions.definition: A type of coarse cotton fabric covered in many small raised loops that is used to make towels , bathrobes and some types of nappy / diaper .
( Commonwealth , dated ) Any makeshift cloth nappy folded from a large piece of absorbent fabric and held in place by a nappy pin or nappy fastener ; a flat nappy .
